    Timekeeping

    Timekeeping

    Search

    Approval

    Reports

    Note:Both supervisors and users can utilize the timekeeping feature. Most time keeping functionalities require a time slice to be enabled, including,approvals, generating reports, conducting searches.

    The Timekeeping tab allows users to input timesheet data, which can be later searched and approved by supervisors or administrators. Users with appropriate permissions can also add crew members to form teams for task assignments. Additionally, this tab facilitates the creation of timekeeping reports.

    A "time slice" refers to the duration of an activity, an example is a time slice for a lunch break. A timesheet consists of multiple consecutive time slices that cover a day's work. Field technicians are required to log time spent on each task, creating slices in the system to document completed work for the day.

    Crew leads have additional privileges, including adding crew members, inputting timesheet data for them, and submitting timesheets for both themselves and their crew. Timesheet data can be added manually or by opening a work item and adding it to the timesheet.

    Functionalities within timekeeping include

    - Timekeeping Searches

    - Timekeeping Approvals

    - Crew management

    - Timekeeping Reports

    Search

    Users can utilize the Search Timesheets tab to monitor timesheets and their statuses. Crew leads can view timesheets submitted by themselves and their crew members. Search parameters can be adjusted to narrow down results.

    Steps to create a search

    1. In the IWMS Client application, click the Timekeeping

    2. Enter data in one or more fields on the Search Timesheets page to narrow down your search and get the required timesheets

    3. Click Search.

    4. The results should be displayed.

    Max results:This drop-down allows the user to select the maximum number of results they want displayed from the search.varying from 50,100,200,500,1000 and 2000.

    Saved searches:

    You can utilize the Saved Searches feature to establish and retain specific search parameters. This enables you to swiftly retrieve necessary records without the need to input search criteria repeatedly when browsing timesheets.

    Steps to saving a search:

    1. Navigate to the Timekeeping section within the IWMS Client application.
    2. Input data into one or more fields on the Search Timesheets page to refine your search and obtain the desired timesheets.
    3. Initiate the search by clicking on the Search button.
    4. Click on the adjacent Save icon next to the Saved Searches button.

    A dialog box titled Save Search will appear.

    5. Enter a descriptive name for the saved search in the Name field. This name will be used when selecting a saved search.

    1. From the Grid Preference list, choose a column preference. This will determine which columns are displayed based on the selected grid preference. For further details on grid preferences, refer to the Configure grid preferences section.
    2. If you wish to designate this saved search as the default, tick the Make This My Default Saved Search checkbox.
    3. Confirm your selections by clicking OK.
    4. Access Saved Searches. The name of the newly created saved search will be visible.

    Manage crews

    You can use the Manage Crews button to manage your crew members. You can add or remove crew members.

    The following page opens after you click on manage crews:

    Export

    You can use the Excel Export button to export the searched records to a Microsoft Excel file. You can select the required items from the grid or can export all the items to a Microsoft Excel file.

    Clear search

    Clears the search that was previously made.All fields that were previously filled will now be empty allowing you to start the search afresh.

    Saved searches

    Allows you to save a filter that you have made for future use.

    Print and Export

    This button allows you to print and Export.

    This button allows you to delete previous searches.**

    Summary View:**

    You can use the Summary View button to view the summary of the timesheets based on the search result that is displayed. You can open the Summary View dialog box by clicking the Summary View button.

    Toggle grouping

    You can utilize the Toggle Grouping button to enable toggle grouping when the search results in the grid are grouped by selecting columns displayed in the grid. By employing toggle grouping, you can expand or collapse the rows shown in the grid.

    To toggle groups:

    1. In the search results grid, click on Toggle Grouping.

    2. The rows in the grid will be expanded. You can click on Summary View to collapse the rows.

    Grid preference

    Instead of a static table, the application shows your data in a customizable grid. This grid lets you pick which columns to display, drag them to change order, and even hide ones you don't need, allowing you to save these preferences as different views.

    Timekeeping Approvals

    Note: The final approval is done only on the admin portal (IWMS Web Portal application*-> Time Keeping*-> Time Keeping Approvals ).The admin can approve the Timesheet using grid or timeslice. Supervisors can approve timesheets on the Approval page. Pre-approvers, designated by supervisors, can pre-approve timesheets, streamlining the approval process. Users can utilize various functions on the Approval page, such as viewing all pending time slices or approving/rejecting them collectively.

    Steps to approve timesheet from the Client application:

    Note:The approval function is only available for allowed Supervisor or a Crewlead. This can also be done in the

    1. Navigate to IWMS application then Time Keeping tab then Approvals.

    The Timekeeping Approval page is displayed.

    2. Click Current Pay Period or Previous Pay Period.

    3. Enter the timekeeping approval details in the following fields.

    Field

    Description

    AOR Dropdown

    Select an AOR.

    Note: Click Check all to select all the AORs check boxes. Click Uncheck all to clear all the AORs check boxes. Also, you can select or clear one or more AOR check boxes.

    Work Location Dropdown

    Select the work location, which is one of the following: User or Timeslice.

    Crew Lead Dropdown

    Select the crew lead name.

    Crew Member Dropdown

    Select the crew member name.

    WO # Field

    Type a work order number.

    Note: If you are not aware of the work order number, do not enter a number in the WO # box. You can locate the required work order number from the search results.

    Structure # Field

    Enter a structure number.

    PERNR Field

    Enter a personal identification number.

    Task Action Dropdown

    Select a task action.Based on the task action you select, the Task Description list is populated.

    Status Dropdown

    Select a status.

    Note: Click Check all to select all the checkboxes. Click Uncheck all to clear all the checkboxes. Also, you can select or clear one or more checkboxes.

    The list differs based on the logged on user.

    • If the logged on user is a Supervisor, the statuses are as follows: Approved, Approved Not Submitted, Editing, Pre-Approved, Pre-Approved Not Submitted, Rejected, Rejected Not Submitted, and Released.
    • If the logged on user is a Crew Lead, the statuses are as follows: Editing, Pre-Approved, Pre-Approved Not Submitted, Rejected, Rejected Not Submitted, and Released.

    Pay Type Dropdown

    Select a pay type.

    Based on the pay type you select, the A/A Type list is populated.

    A/A Type Dropdown

    Select an A/A Type.

    Based on the pay type you select, the Comp. Type list is populated. The Comp Type list is populated when the options selected in the Pay Type list and the A/A Type list are related to compensation.

    Comp. Type Dropdown

    Select the compensation type.

    Circuit/Section

    To select an circuit or section, do one of the following:

    • In the Filter box, enter the first few characters of the circuit or section that you want to search.
    • Click Check all to select all the checkboxes. Click Uncheck all to clear all the checkboxes. Also you can select or clear one or more checkboxes.

    Max Results

    Select the maximum number of results to be displayed during search.

    Upgrade Code

    Select an upgraded code.

    Shift Pay

    Select a shift pay.

    Problem Code

    Select a problem code.

    From

    Select a from date.

    To

    Select a to date.

    Seq/MSR # Field

    Enter the sequence number or the Meter Service Request number.

    Address Field

    Type the address.

    Printing and Exporting Timesheets

    You can use the Print and Export to print the timesheet data. You need to select the timesheets and click the Print and Export icon to generate the required report.

    Crew Management

    You can use the Crew Management page to manage your crew members. The crew management page allows you to :

    -Add crew members

    -Remove crew members.

    -Add a subcrew

    -Remove a subcrew

    Add Crew members

    You can add crew members to your crew. To add members to your crew, you must search the members. After a crew member is added, you can view or submit timesheets for the crew member.

    To add a crew member:

    1. In the IWMS Client application, click the Timekeeping.
    2. The Timekeeping group is displayed.
    3. In the Timekeeping group, click Crew Management.

    The Crew Management page is displayed.

    1. In the Add Crew Members section, do one or more of the following:
      1. In the First Name box, type a member's first name, fully or partially.
      2. In the Last Name box, type a member's last name, fully or partially.
      3. In the AOR list, select an area. You can click Select All to widen the result.

    5. Click Search.

    The members that pass the earlier three filters are displayed in the grid.

    6. Select the check boxes adjacent to one or more member names to add the crew members.The Add button in the Add Crew Members section is made available.

    7. Click Add.

    Remove Crew members

    You can remove crew members from your crew. After you remove a crew member from your crew, you cannot view the timesheet details of the removed member.

    To remove a crew member:

    1. In the IWMS Client application, click the Timekeeping.
    2. The Timekeeping group is displayed.In the Timekeeping group, click Crew Management.
    3. The Crew Management page is displayed. In the Crew Management section, select the one or more checkboxes adjacent to the members' names that you want to remove.
    4. The Remove Crew Member button is made available.Click Remove Crew Member.

    1. The system displays an alert message asking you to confirm whether to remove the selected one or more crew members.Click Yes to remove the crew member.

    The crew member is removed from the grid.

    Add Subcrew

    You can group your crew members by creating a subcrew and moving the members to the respective groups. You can use the subcrew as a filter to quickly identify the crew members in that specific subcrew.

    To add a sub-crew:

    1. In the IWMS Client application, click the Timekeeping.
    2. The Timekeeping group is displayed.In the Timekeeping group, click Crew Management.
    3. The Crew Management page is displayed. In the Crew Management section, click Add Sub-Crew.
    4. A new tab with the title Double Click to Rename is added in the Crew Management section.Double-click the tab title, and then type a name for the subcrew.

    1. It is recommended to name a subcrew that helps you identify the members in the sub crew, by reading the subcrew title. For example, if the crew members in the subcrew are from the same geographical region, you can use the name of the area.In the Crew Management section, on the All Crew Members tab, do one of the following:
      1. Right-click the member name that you want to move to this subcrew.
      2. Select the check boxes adjacent to the members' names to move multiple crew members to a sub crew, and then right-click the selected rows in the grid.
    2. The Move to pop-up menu is displayed. On the Move to pop-up menu, right-click to display all sub crews, and then click a subcrew name.

    The crew members are displayed in the clicked sub crew.

    Remove Subcrew

    You can remove a subcrew on the Crew Management page, if you do not require the subcrew. For example, if you have created a subcrew by the name of an area, and most crew members in the subcrew are assigned to another work area.

    To remove a sub-crew:

    1. In the IWMS Client application, click the Timekeeping.
    2. The Timekeeping group is displayed.In the Timekeeping group, click Crew Management.
    3. The Crew Management page is displayed. In the Crew Management section, select a subcrew.
    4. The members in the subcrew are displayed in a grid. The Remove Sub-Crew button is made available.Click Remove Sub-Crew.

    The selected subcrew is removed from the Crew Management section.

    Reports

    Various reports can be generated by selecting the appropriate option, including CMS Reports, Contract Interpreted Reports, and SAP Reports. Time slices are required to generate these reports.Note:An error notification shows up when you click on either of the reports,requiring you to connect to the server.
